# =====================================================================
# Unity Specific Files
# =====================================================================

# Library folder: Contains cached data, local settings, and GUIDs. MUST be ignored.
/[Ll]ibrary/

# Temp folder: Temporary files generated during runtime/compilation.
/[Tt]emp/

# Object folder: Intermediate build files.
/[Oo]bj/

# Build folder: Final build outputs (if you build locally).
/[Bb]uild/
/[Bb]uilds/

# Logs: Runtime logs.
*.log
*.pdb

# Visual Studio / IDE Specific Files
.vs/
.vscode/
*.csproj
*.unityproj
*.sln

# Meta files: Unity generates .meta files for every asset. 
# These are generally tracked, but sometimes large or unstable ones can be ignored.
# NOTE: For standard workflow, keep .meta files! They store GUIDs necessary for linking assets.
# If you are using Git LFS, you MUST NOT ignore .meta files unless you are tracking them via LFS too.

# =====================================================================
# Git LFS Configuration
# =====================================================================

# Git LFS tracks large files by replacing them with small pointer files.
# You must configure LFS to track specific binary extensions in a separate .gitattributes file.
# Do NOT ignore the file extensions you want LFS to manage here.